In this code, we first lock the mutex to ensure thread safety. Then we allocate a new buffer with the size of the data in the KeylogBuffer plus one for the null termination character. If the allocation fails, we set the length to 0 and return nullptr. Otherwise, we copy the data from the KeylogBuffer to the new buffer, add a null termination character, set the length, and reset the index i to 0. Finally, we return the new buffer.

